<TEXT>
a gunman who held police at bay for 5 hours 
friday ended the standoff by shooting himself in the head and 
falling from atop a 16story building in one of the citys busiest 
neighborhoods authorities said 
paul a fisher 30 of pittsburgh was propelled forward off an 
apartment buildings roof by a single shot from a handgun about 
510 pm said police chief mayer deroy he was pronounced dead at 
the scene 
no one on the ground was injured 
he said he was going to jump since we wouldnt assassinate 
him deroy said 
fisher who had a history of mental illness and problems at 
home apparently was trying to draw attention to himself on the 
apartment buildings roof deroy said 
he wore a bright orange hat and blue shortsleeved shirt and 
had 50 rounds of ammunition in a duffel bag deroy said 
about noon fisher fired one shot from a 22caliber rifle at an 
unmarked police car and 11 other rifle shots into the air police 
said 
two roman catholic schools were evacuated and a four to 
fiveblock area was blocked off to traffic 
police believed they were making progress 15 minutes before 
fisher killed himself because he turned over the rifle to police 
negotiators 
fisher climbed a drainpipe to get to the roofs tallest parapet 
and smoked a cigarette on a ledge deroy said 
he then put the gun to his head and pulled the trigger the 
chief said i told him we werent interested in prosecuting him 
criminally we were only interested in getting him help 
fisher killed himself before hundreds of onlookers and several 
tv crews local pittsburgh newscasts did not air the videotape 
while national cnn headline news did 
he told police he was up on the roof half an hour with weapons 
and no one was paying attention to him so he fired at the unmarked 
police car with the 22caliber rifle 
deroy said the man threw scrap paper over the side of the 
building to see how long it took to fall to the ground 
fisher fired the first shot at an unmarked police car shortly 
before noon said assistant police chief donald aubrecht over the 
next several hours he fired several other rounds into the air and 
occasionally pointed the rifle at the ground without shooting 
police sharpshooters took up positions on rooftops near the 
16story moorehead towers said public safety spokeswoman margaret 
philbin the building houses the elderly and handicapped in the 
citys oakland section 
four police officers tried to talk with the sniper from a 
stairway on the outside of the building ms philbin said 
all he wants is a coke and cigarettes they threw him a 
bunch she said 
more than 50 police officers were at the scene and cordoned off 
an area of about four or five blocks around the building snarling 
traffic in the heavily populated area near the university of 
pittsburgh 
students at two roman catholic schools near the apartments were 
led out the schools back doors to safety and continued classes at 
another school also in oakland 
