muckraking and acid commentary has suggested a scenario that is 
both humorous and chilling 
the newspapers political fantasy published aug 26 begins 
with staunch soviet support for iraqs aug 2 invasion of kuwait 
it ends with soviet and western ships steaming toward a military 
showdown along the way it satirizes communist rhetoric and 
official pronouncements 
in reality gorbachev condemned the iraqi invasion cut off arms 
shipments to saddam endorsed an economic embargo against iraq and 
supported a un security council resolution allowing navies to use 
force to maintain the embargo 
here in abbreviated form is moscow news fictional scenario of 
what might have happened if leonid brezhnev or someone like him 
were still running the soviet union 
