from attending the weeklong seventh congress on crime that closed 
friday 
the cuban government of fidel castro had no immediate public 
comment on the incidents dispatches on the conference by the 
official cuban news agency prensa latina from havana monitored in 
the mexican capital made no mention of them 
all five league delegates including three havana residents and 
prominent cuban human rights activists opposed to president 
castros communist regime were previously approved by the un 
the league said 
one of them yndamiro restano is a member of the cuban 
commission for human rights and national reconciliation 
another antonio de varona batlle served as defense counsel for 
