monday for a twoday trip to kwajalein atoll an army missile test 
range in the pacific 
antiballistic missile radar is prohibited by the 1972 abm 
treaty between the united states and the soviet union 
john pike head of space policy at the federation of american 
scientists and a star wars critic said the aircraft appears to 
be the functional equivalent of an abm radar 
pike said the soviets may be justified in questioning whether 
the airborne sensor is a treaty violation 
if we saw the russians doing this kind of thing we would be 
pretty bent out of shape about it and if the russians were giving 
the explanation we are we wouldnt believe them pike said 
the army says the airborne sensor is not a prototype for an 
antimissile sensor system it also argues that the aircraft could 
not substitute for an abm radar because of technical limitations in 
its infrared sensor and its onboard computers 
