finance ministers of the 12member european 
community today discussed plans for economic and monetary union and 
assessed the impact of the persian gulf crisis on europes economy 
on friday ec foreign ministers agreed to give 2 billion in 
economic aid to turkey jordan and egypt to compensate them for 
lost trade with iraq the united nations has imposed an economic 
embargo on iraq for its aug 2 invasion of kuwait 
officials said the finance ministers would discuss how the aid 
will be financed italy holds the rotating presidency of the 
european community 
the ec hopes the oilrich persian gulf nations notably saudi 
arabia which benefits from higher oil prices will pay 6 billion 
of the estimated 9 billion turkey jordan and egypt will lose 
through 1991 
ec economic and monetary affairs commissioner henning 
christophersen will give the finance ministers an initial 
assessment of the impact of the gulf crisis on the ec economy 
he will not offer precise figures officials said but present 
several scenarios including one foreseeing oil prices hovering at 
around 30 a barrel at that price the communitys economic growth 
could drop to 21 percent from a forecast rate of 31 percent and 
there would be a reversal in the trend toward declining 
unemployment according to ec figures 
another key topic of todays meeting was plans to turn the 
european community into an economic and monetary union an issue 
that has pitted britain against its ec partners 
in december the 12 ec nations will hold a conference to amend 
the communitys constitution creating a european central bank and 
a single currency 
while there is agreement on the need to turn the ec into a more 
effective trade bloc there are disagreements on the need for a 
single currency and central bank both of which britain opposes 
the finance ministers today discussed a blueprint for economic 
and monetary union that proposes a european central banking system 
called eurofed as early as jan 1 1993 and a european currency 
unit the ecu to become a single ec currency 
spain today proposed the ec not create a single currency until 
at least 2000 but use the currency along with the 12 national 
currencies for several years before the switch 
spanish finance minister carlos solchaga also recommended the ec 
not establish eurofed until after jan 1 1994 
the european community members are france west germany italy 
luxembourg belgium the netherlands denmark greece ireland 
portugal spain and the united kingdom 
