expected to have much direct influence on saudi society because 
most are stationed at desert bases it is the first time foreigners 
have been called in to defend the kingdom 
in addition a call for army volunteers represents a major 
change in a force that had been reserved for princes and members of 
the bedouin tribes loyal to the ruling alsaud family since the 
country was united in the 1920s 
they used to look for what was referred to as a friendship of 
arms bagour said now the doors been thrown wide open 
billions of dollars in oil money engendered a false sense of 
security in saudi arabia and the spartan desert warrior tradition 
gave way to limousines and air conditioning 
the saudi government has pampered its citizens for years 
given them everything for free said khaled a almaeena editor 
