a network of more than 4000 princes but businessmen are privately 
critical of the growing number of princes who use their influence 
to win government contracts 
king fahd is an absolute monarch like the neighboring emirates 
and sheikdoms saudi arabia has little democratic structure but 
that could be changing one option is a consultative council the 
government built a headquarters for it in the 1980s but did not 
name a council or hold elections 
because of the small population somewhere between 7 and 11 
million in an area the size of western europe policy changes could 
increase opportunities for women 
conscription for men has historically opened a place for women 
