<TEXT>
the 265th quartermaster detachment of the south 
carolina national guard is one of the reserve units called up for 
possible duty in saudi arabia national writer fred bayles is 
following the 14 guardsmen as they prepare for deployment overseas 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
it looks like christmas gone mad 
plastic soldier targets lit like holiday lawn ornaments are 
under assault orange tracers slice through them like death rays 
bullets ricochet and flare with brief rosecolored intensity a 
bush catches fire illuminating the night 
the 265th quartermaster detachment a water purification unit of 
the south carolina national guard is practicing night fire 
another skill they needed for duty in the mideast 
some of the 14 men all from the environs of allendale sc 
are exhilarated by the sound and light show they have staged 
we are ready we are ready shouted don graham a 
construction supervisor as they drove back to the barracks through 
the sultry night some of the other men had already fallen asleep 
there was little enthusiasm earlier in the day as the 265th a 
collection of civilians that includes construction workers prison 
guards a truck driver and a college student spent a long hot and 
dusty afternoon on the range sweating swearing and firing at 
popup targets that sometimes failed to popup 
the day begins with an almost picnic quality the air is filled 
with dragonflies and vibrant orange and yellow butterflies that 
flitter and land on the flat black muzzles of the m16s 
there is even a picnic lunch of mres meals readytoeat 
booksized foil packages that come in a variety of flavors 
one of the many delicacies is tuna with noodles a lukewarm glop 
of casserole that comes with separate packages of 
fortified cheese spread knead package before opening 
crackers 
chocolate nut cake 
beverage base powder grape 
as the name implies you open the packages and eat but there 
are table manners to be learned you can heat the meal by placing 
the package in the sun and you might want to think twice about 
putting the grape mix in your canteen 
you better be sure you like it cause your waters going to 
taste like that forever warns sgt earnest deloach 
but haute cuisine only goes so far the bucolic scene becomes 
oppressive as the day grows long and the temperature soars into the 
90s worst of all the unit must don hellishly hot chemical 
protective overclothes and the everpresent gas mask and try to 
knock down targets 
bullets fly wide and heads ache from the kevlar helmets you 
feel like the helmet has melted through your softened skull and 
imbedded itself in your brain 
my head hurts im covered with dirt im sweated through the 
only way im going to make it is if the good lord lets me said 
spec ulysses calhoun as he struggled out of his chemical warfare 
suit 
the targets just arent falling says spec mark rooker 
rooker 20 is the youngest and newest member of the unit when 
the other men stop to check out female personnel rooker wanders 
over to check out the tanks and armored personnel carriers 
he carries a large survival knife on his web gear and asks 
hopefully about getting an m203 grenade launcher for his rifle 
rooker wanted to join a national guard firefighters unit but 
his training school would have interfered with college so he took 
a less exciting option the 265th water purification unit 
it has turned out to be anything but boring 
i could be home right now working in an air conditioned 
bank he said i guess i made a mistake 
