rainbow an 11yearold 8foot2 450pound male bluegray 
bottlenose dolphin would be swapped for a partly deaf female in the 
navys secret underwater mammal program at the naval ocean systems 
center in san diego 
we are vehemently opposed to any dolphin being given to the 
navy under any circumstances said doreen close a spokeswoman 
for the boston marine mammal coalition once they get into the 
navys hands we have no way of knowing what happens to them 
john h prescott the aquariums executive director said public 
