following are excerpts translated from 
arabic by the associated press from iraqi president saddam 
husseins message to presidents bush and mikhail gorbachev on the 
eve of the superpower summit 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
your meeting will be watched with keen and unusual interest by 
the whole world including the peoples of a region which god 
blessed by making us a part of the arab nation 
i will neither plead with you nor dictate what decisions you 
must adopt because each of you has his own will and freedom of 
decision 
but before you make whatever decisions you will i would like 
to begin by saying that iraqs army did not invade either of your 
countries and has no intention to harm anyone or jeopardize the 
legitimate interests of anyone iraq is a peaceloving nation we 
desire peace which is based on justice iraq respects the free 
decision of others 
before either of you make a decision on kuwait you should 
remember that the arab nation is one nation even though it is 
split now that this is a fact that cannot be denied by its rulers 
leaders peoples or sons that the overwhelming majority of its 
sons rulers and peoples are honored to be part of this great 
nation and that they are longing to be one political entity 
regardless of the specific characteristics of this or that country 
 
kuwait is part of iraq the kuwaiti people are part of the 
iraqi people british colonialism severed it from iraq for colonial 
reasons iraq did not recognize this measure 
any attempt to reverse the situation to what it was before 
aug 2 1990 is an impractical and sterile attempt that will push 
the region into chaos furthermore the attempts aimed at promoting 
the instability constitute a premeditated conspiracy against the 
arab nation at the head of which is lofty iraq 
when you consider these facts in their proper perspective and 
show humility once you know the rights of mankind you will realize 
that the arabs by their recollection of the relevant background on 
the basis of these facts are more capable than others of resolving 
all interarab affairs 
you will also then realize that foreigners including 
yourselves are incapable of offering the proper solution 
neither of you is capable of providing a proper settlement of 
an arab problem whose parties are arabs we can swear and god and 
history are witness to this that the foreign intervention is 
complicating matters and will not provide a settlement 
the occupation and invasion of the prophets birthplace and 
tomb is an insult directed not only against the 200 million arabs 
but the 1 billion moslems 
they will join and pool all resources to resist this obscene 
act and defeat the oppressors 
every politician knows the united states and for awhile now 
has been manipulating the world and dictating its terms with no one 
standing up to confront it as the case was before 
those concerned with this problem should take advantage of 
this crucial time in history and employ this critical problem to 
restore to the soviet union its respect as a decisive power 
through adopting a position that is in harmony with all that is 
just and fair and rejecting the discriminatory approach the united 
states is pursuing 
i pray that the merciful allow you to take decisions that 
would allow some light into the hearts of the heartless espcially 
bush in the interest of humanity at large 
president bush must not bring his country and its status down 
to a lower level because we are certain that its position will 
drop on the scale of appreciation and effectiveness if it falls 
into the abyss of war and if its armies and the armies of its 
allies remain in the land of our sanctuaries and if it continues 
this unjustified and cruel blockade which is depriving the people 
of iraq of food and medicine and cutting off the supply of milk 
from children who need it 
the iraqi people will stand united against injustice and the 
unjust and against the invasion and the invaders the traitors 
who encouraged those who have been deluded will be a small 
minority 
when the battle has taken place then the iraqi people whom 
god has chosen to be in the forefront will triumph and all the 
invaders will be defeated their banners torn apart and deafened 
by the shouts of god is great and damned be the invaders 
</TEXT>
