hurricane isidore lost strength and became a 
tropical storm saturday as it moved northwest at 14 mph over open 
water 
the storms maximum sustained winds were 65 mph and it was about 
1050 miles northwest of the cape verde islands the national 
hurricane center reported the storm was located near latitude 284 
north and longitude 399 west at 445 pm 
