a mohawk warrior and two soldiers were injured 
saturday in a scuffle on the kahnesatake settlement west of 
montreal where canadian troops were locked in a standoff with a 
group of armed indians 
mohawk spokesmen said a 51yearold mohawk was awakened in his 
sleep and severely beaten by soldiers 
